Consider the commutative diagram
\usepackage {amsmath} \usepackage {amssymb} \usepackage {tikz-cd} \begin {tikzcd}[row sep=huge] \operatorname {H}^1(X,\mathbb {Z}(1)) \ar [r,"\sim "] \ar [d] \ar [dr,phantom,"1"] & \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^1(X, [\mathcal {O}_X\xrightarrow {\exp }\mathcal {O}_X^*]) \ar [d] \ar [dr,phantom,"2"] & \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^1(\overline {X}, [j_*\mathcal {O}_X\xrightarrow {\exp }j_*\mathcal {O}_X^*]) \ar [l,swap,"\sim "] \ar [d] \ar [dr,phantom,"3"] & \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^1(\overline {X}, [\mathcal {O}_{\overline {X}}\xrightarrow {\exp }j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathcal {O}_X^*]) \ar [l,swap,"\sim "] \ar [d] \\\operatorname {H}^1(X,\mathbb {C}) \ar [r] & \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^1(X, [\mathcal {O}_X\xrightarrow {\mathrm {d}}r_*\Omega _{\overline {X}'}^1]) & \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^1(\overline {X}, [j_*\mathcal {O}_X\to j_*r_*\Omega _{X'}^1]) \ar [l] & \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^1(\overline {X}, [\mathcal {O}_{\overline {X}}\to r_*\Omega _{\overline {X}'}^1(\log S)]) \ar [l,swap,"\sim "] \end {tikzcd}

The horizontal arrows in the square labelled 1 are isomorphisms, since the sequences \begin {gathered} 0 \to \mathbb {Z}(1) \to \mathcal {O}_X \xrightarrow {\exp } \mathcal {O}_X^* \to 0 \\0 \to \mathbb {C} \to \mathcal {O}_X \xrightarrow {\mathrm {d}} r_*\Omega _{X'}^1 \to 0 \end {gathered} are exact. Those in 2 are isomorphisms since \mathrm {R}^1j_*\mathcal {O}_X=0. Those in 3 are isomorphisms since the morphisms of the complexes that define them are quasi-isomorphisms. This diagram defines the desired construction.

html:ol.html:li: Let j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathcal {O}_X^* be the subsheaf of meromorphic functions in j_*\mathcal {O}_X^*. We have that \operatorname {H}^1(X,\mathbb {Z}(1)) = \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^1(\overline {X},[\mathcal {O}_{\overline {X}}\xrightarrow {\exp }j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathcal {O}_X^*]).

The inclusion of \operatorname {H}^1(X,\mathbb {Z}) into \operatorname {H}^1(X,\mathbb {C}) is defined by the morphism of complexes \begin {CD} \mathcal {O}_{\overline {X}} @>{\exp }>> j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathcal {O}_X^* \\@V{\simeq }VV @VV{\mathrm {d} f/f}V \\\mathcal {O}_{\overline {X}} @>>> r_*\Omega _{\overline {X}'}^1(\log S) \end {CD}
